#Text=The San Antonio Spurs ( 26 - 16 ) defeated the Utah Jazz ( 14 - 27 ) 89 - 69 on Sunday at the AT & T Center in San Antonio .
#Text=In this very low scoring matchup , both teams struggled from the field .
#Text=The Spurs went 39 percent from the floor and 47 percent from the three - point line , while the Jazz went just 33 percent from the field and 30 percent from the three - point line .
#Text=The Spurs were able to take the advantage from the free throw line as well , converting on 19 - of - 23 attempts , while the Jazz made only 10 - of - 16 attempts .
#Text=The Jazz also struggled with turnovers , as they committed 15 throughout the game .
#Text=The Spurs were led by Tiago Splitter , who finished with 14 points ( 5 - 12 FG , 4 - 4 FT ) and four rebounds in just under 22 minutes .
#Text=He 's only reached double figures in points six other times this season , so it was good to see him have a productive outing .
#Text=Danny Green had a solid showing , going 5 - for - 7 from the field and 3 - for - 4 from the three - point line to score 13 points , while adding six rebounds .
#Text=He 's been very productive for the Spurs over his last three games , averaging 17 points over that span .
#Text=Coming one rebound shy of a double - double , Kawhi Leonard posted 12 points ( 4 - 11 FG , 1 - 2 3Pt ) and nine rebounds .
#Text=After returning from an injury on Friday that had kept him out of the lineup for a month , Leonard recorded 20 points , so he came back down to earth a little bit in this matchup .
#Text=Both Tony Parker and Tim Duncan played limited minutes , scoring four ( 2 - 5 FG ) and 12 points ( 3 - 8 FG , 5 - 6 FT ) respectively .
#Text=Also coming off the bench , Aron Baynes added a double - double with 12 points and 11 rebounds .
#Text=The Jazz just could n't get in a rhythm offensively against the Spurs , as only two players reached double figures in points .
#Text=Coming off the bench , Rudy Gobert led the team in , scoring 13 points and grabbing an impressive 18 rebounds in 28 minutes .
#Text=The 18 points were a new season - high for him , while the double - double was his sixth on the season .
#Text=Gordon Hayward really struggled with his shot , going only 4 - for - 15 from the field and 1 - for - 2 from the three - point line to score 10 points .
#Text=After scoring 31 points on Friday , he was n't able to have a repeat performance and scored well under his season average of 19 points per game .
#Text=While he came one point shy of reaching double figures in points , Derrick Favors added nine points ( 4 - 11 FG , 1 - 2 FT ) , 13 rebounds and four blocked shots .
#Text=This game was the first time in seven matchups that he did n't have at least 15 points .
#Text=The Spurs ' next game will be on the road against the Denver Nuggets on Tuesday , while the Jazz will travel to Cleveland to play the Cavaliers on Wednesday .
